outh carolina historical and genealogical magazine south carolina historical society  p    letitia ellicott carpenter wright  colonial garden at stenton described in old letters pp – i cannot boast of a turn for botany tho if i had  could spare the time from my other affairs i should have great advantage from my intimacy with doctor garden whom you have doubtless heard of i desire you will send me a list of the flowers and shrubs you have in your garden  i will try with the help of my friend the doctor to make your collection more compleat lord adam gordon is now here and will leave these parts about the beginning of march to finish a tour of this continent as far as from mobile to quebeck consequently he will take philadelphia in his way he has a very pretty botanical turn is very new and curious in his observation i will recommend him to your acquaintance and i am certain you will be much pleased with his he will give you a very particular account of the plants of this country i beg you will make my respectful compliments acceptable to mrs logan and that you will remember me kindly to mr pemberton i wish you many returns of the new year and am with real esteem your most obdt servt john gordon   lord adam gordon c  keith w murray ed a manuscript by lord adam gordon pdf p    lord adam gordon  journal of an officers travels in america and the west indies  in newton dennison mereness travels in the american colonies the macmillan company p    nicholas michael butler  votaries of apollo the st cecilia society and the patronage of concert music in charleston south carolina  univ of south carolina press p  isbn    alexia jones helsley  a guide to historic beaufort south carolina the history press p  isbn    the south carolina historical and genealogical magazine south carolina historical society  pp ra   national genealogical society quarterly the society  p    alexander samuel salley  marriage notices in the southcarolina gazette and its successors  j munsells sons pp –